# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Step-by-step Deobfuscation

The code is heavily obfuscated using several techniques:
1. **String encoding** - RC4 encryption + Base64 for all strings
2. **Control flow flattening** - Switch statements with shuffled cases
3. **Dead code injection** - Fake branches and unreachable code
4. **Anti-debugging/anti-tampering** - Self-defending mechanisms
5. **Hex/unicode escape sequences** for all property names

## What It Actually Does

After stripping away all the obfuscation layers, this is a **2D force-directed graph simulation** (like a physics-based node layout). Here's the cleaned version:

```javascript
// === CONSTANTS ===
const TWO_PI = 6.283; // ~2π
const GOLDEN_RATIO = 0.618;
const SQRT_HALF = 0.707; // ~√0.5

const config = {
    particleCount: 4000,
    attractionCoeff: 0.004,
    amplitudeDamping: 0.92,
    universal: 0.0003,      // universal gravity/centering force
    streamLimit: 40,         // max particles
    streamDecay: 0.04,
    smoothing: 0.06
};

// === NODES (graph vertices) ===
const nodes = [
    { id: "hub",      label: "Hub",      r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",     label: "Beta",     r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",    label: "Gamma",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",    label: "Delta",    r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon",  label: "Epsilon",  r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "electron", label: "Electron", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// === EDGES (springs between nodes) ===
const edges = [
    { a: "hub",     b: "beta",     rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub",     b: "gamma",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "beta",    b: "epsilon",  rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "gamma",   b: "epsilon",  rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "delta",   b: "electron", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha",   b: "delta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "hub",     b: "delta",    rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha",   b: "electron", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// === CAMERA / VIEWPORT ===
let camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
let target = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// === PARTICLES (visual effect) ===
let particles = [];
let frame = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// === PHYSICS: Apply forces ===
function applyForces() {
    // Node-to-node repulsion (all pairs)
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            let dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            let dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            let force = config.universal / (dist * dist);

            let fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            let fy = (dy / dist) * force;

            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // Spring forces along edges
    for (let p = 0; p < edges.length; p++) {
        let A = findNode(edges[p].a);
        let X = findNode(edges[p].b);
        if (!A || !X) continue;

        let dx = X.x - A.x;
        let dy = X.y - A.y;
        let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        let displacement = dist - edges[p].rest;
        let force = (edges[p].k || config.attractionCoeff) * displacement;

        A.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        A.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        X.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        X.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // Update positions: apply velocity, damping, and centering force
    for (let S = 0; S < nodes.length; S++) {
        // Centering force (pulls toward canvas center ~400,300)
        nodes[S].vx += (400 - nodes[S].x) * config.universal;
        nodes[S].vy += (300 - nodes[S].y) * config.universal;

        // Velocity damping
        nodes[S].vx *= config.amplitudeDamping;
        nodes[S].vy *= config.amplitudeDamping;

        // Integrate position
        nodes[S].x += nodes[S].vx;
        nodes[S].y += nodes[S].vy;
    }
}

// === PARTICLE EMITTER ===
function emitParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.streamLimit) return;

    let source = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    let angle = Math.random() * TWO_PI;
    let speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

    particles.push({
        x: source.x,
        y: source.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 100 + Math.random() * 200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * GOLDEN_RATIO * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// === PARTICLE UPDATER ===
function updateParticles() {
    for (let R = particles.length - 1; R >= 0; R--) {
        let p = particles[R];

        p.age++;
        p.vx *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;

        // Remove expired particles
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(R, 1);
        }
    }
}

// === CAMERA SMOOTHING ===
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (target.x - camera.x) * config.smoothing;
    camera.y += (target.y - camera.y) * config.smoothing;
    camera.zoom += (target.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.smoothing;
}

// === MAIN LOOP ===
function tick() {
    applyForces();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    frame++;
    if (frame % 3 === 0) emitParticle();
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60fps
```

## Summary

This is a **force-directed graph visualization engine** with:

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| **6 nodes** | Named entities (Hub, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon, Electron) with positions, radii, and velocities |
| **8 edges** | Spring connections between nodes with rest lengths and spring constants |
| **Repulsion forces** | Nodes push each other apart (Coulomb's law style) |
| **Spring forces** | Edges pull connected nodes toward their rest length (Hooke's law) |
| **Centering force** | Gentle pull toward canvas center (400, 300) |
| **Velocity damping** | 0.92 multiplier per frame prevents runaway motion |
| **Particle system** | Decorative particles emitted from random nodes, fading over time |
| **Smooth camera** | Viewport that interpolates toward a target position/zoom |
| **Anti-tampering** | Self-defending code that detects debugging/modification attempts |

The anti-debugging layers include:
- **Console detection** — detects if dev tools console is open
- **Debugger traps** — `while(true) debugger` patterns
- **Self-integrity checks** — verifies the code hasn't been modified via regex matching against its own source
- **Domain validation** — appears to check allowed hostnames

Essentially: **a physics simulation for an interactive node graph, wrapped in aggressive anti-reverse-engineering protection**.
